<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1436,836,1040]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Originally described as 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1884" box="[474,713,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Lasiochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dilasia">
<emphasis box="[474,713,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Lasiochilus (Dilasia)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Description in Reuter’s Monography (1884: 27) refers to “ ... 
<emphasis box="[151,913,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">tibiae... margine inferiori dense fortiter et profundis serrato-dentato</emphasis>
(as in the present generic key “giving a longer appearence”), 
<emphasis box="[319,818,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">... posterioribus concoloriter spinulosis...”</emphasis>
. The presence of spiniform teeth on the fore- and hindtibiae (as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter, 1871" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1871" baseAuthorityName="B. White" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[337,480,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dilasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denigrata">
<emphasis box="[337,480,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">D. denigrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
B-W., and 
<taxonomicName authority="Usinger" authorityName="Usinger" authorityYear="1871" box="[606,868,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dilasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marianense">
<emphasis box="[606,771,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">D. marianense</emphasis>
Usinger
</taxonomicName>
) and the smooth dorsal surface, justify placing this species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter, 1871" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1871" box="[268,350,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dilasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,350,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Dilasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
